n the following passage some of the words have been left out. Read the passage carefully and select the correct answer for the given blank out of the alternatives. A poor man and his family ate ________ little other residents of the town were kind enough to spare. One day, when he and his family sat down to eat, a stranger _____ and told them that he was hungry. The head of the family gave his _______ to the visitor. Not satisfied with this, the man asked for_______. Finally, the entire food that the family had was _____ to the stranger. Only then did he say that he had ________ enough.

1. so 
2. whatever
3. had
4. however
5. given
6. more
7. every
8. came
9. portion
(7 Points)
